How to Run the Project

Prerequisites
Make sure the following software is installed:
- Python 3.10 or above
- Node.js (v18 or above recommended)
- npm
- Git

1️⃣ Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/Nitheeshsiddegowda/Energy_Consumption_Forecasting_and_Recommendation_Agent_ECFRA.git
cd Energy_Consumption_Forecasting_and_Recommendation_Agent_ECFRA

2️⃣ Backend Setup
Navigate to the backend folder:
cd backend
Create a virtual environment:
# Windows
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
# Linux / macOS
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Apply database migrations:
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate

(Optional) Create an admin user:
python manage.py createsuperuser

Start the Django server:
python manage.py runserver

Backend will run at:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/

3️⃣ Frontend Setup

Open a new terminal.
Navigate to the frontend folder:
cd frontend
Install dependencies:
npm install

Start the React development server:
npm start

Frontend will run at:
http://localhost:3000/

4️⃣ Using the Application

1. Register a new user.
2. Login using your credentials.
3. Upload an energy consumption CSV dataset.
4. View dataset preview.
5. Analyze energy consumption in the Overview page.
6. Explore appliance-wise distribution.
7. Generate energy forecasts.
8. View personalized recommendations.
9. Analyze all insights in the Dashboard.

📂 Dataset

Upload a CSV dataset containing historical household energy consumption.
The dataset should include columns such as:
- Date
- Temperature
- Humidity
- Fan(Units)
- AC(Units)
- TV(Units)
- Fridge(Units)
- Bulb(Units)
- Monitor(Units)
- Motor(Units)
- Units
- ElectricityBill

Authentication
The application uses JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication.
After successful login:
- Access Token is generated.
- Refresh Token is generated.
- Protected routes can only be accessed by authenticated users.

